      <t:profileDesc xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">
         <t:abstract>
            <t:p>This homily normally forms part of the <t:title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1295Dersan">Dǝrsāna Mikāʾel</t:title> collection (usually for Ṭǝrr but sometimes for Miyāzyā), but is also included in some manuscripts of
               the <t:title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2222RetuaH">Rǝtuʿa Hāymānot</t:title> homiliary (e. g. in <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/BNFabb80">Paris, Bibliothèque nationale de France, BnF Éthiopien d'Abbadie 80</t:ref>, <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/EMML7028">ኢትዮጵያ, , MS EMML no. 7028</t:ref>, <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/EMIP01293"><span xmlns="" class="w3-tag w3-red">No item: EMIP01293</span></t:ref>). A variant of the homily sometimes appears for Hamle as <t:ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT3981Homily">Homily on the Archangel Michael by John</t:ref> and also as <t:ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT7176MiracleMichaelTalason">Miracle</t:ref></t:p>
         </t:abstract>
         <t:langUsage><t:language ident="en">English</t:language><t:language ident="gez">Gǝʿǝz</t:language></t:langUsage>
